  "notes": [
    "Transfer Admission Screening Policy Transfer students must complete the following five courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a grade of C (2.0) or better in each course by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: AM 10 – Mathematical Methods for Engineers I AM 20 – Mathematical Methods for Engineers II AM 30 – Multivariate Calculus for Engineers MATH 19A – Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics MATH 19B – Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics Strongly Recommended Major Preparation In addition to the five required major preparation courses, prospective transfer students are strongly advised to complete courses listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" and \"Additional Major Preparation Courses\" sections below, or their articulated equivalents. These courses are prerequisites for the upper-division courses required for this major. Students who do not complete these preparatory courses before transferring will likely need additional quarters of enrollment to finish their degree. Students are strongly encouraged to complete a programming course in either Python or C before transferring. If these courses are not available, students should take a programming course in any language to gain familiarity with general programming concepts and environments. In preparation for upper-division courses taken after transferring, students should complete at least two courses from the \"Additional Major Preparation Courses\" section that corresponds with their primary areas of interest: Earth Sciences, Electrical and Computer Engineering, or Physics: see section A Computer Science and Engineering or Electrical and Computer Engineering: see section B Economics or Statistics: see section C Mathematical Biology: see section D Additional Information for Transfer Students are strongly recommended to complete as many general education requirements as possible before transferring to UC Santa Cruz. This will allow them to focus on upper-division courses required for the major and graduate in a timely manner. For more information on incorporating UC Santa Cruz general education requirements into your pre-transfer academic plan, please consult with your community college counselor. Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this major.",
    "All transfer applicants must satisfy University of California admissions eligibility requirements and campus admission selection criteria. All admission requirements must be completed by the end of spring prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility requirements and admission to UC Santa Cruz, please visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that ensures your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require the completion of specific preparatory courses and/or minimum GPA requirements. For detailed information about the screening requirements for this major, please refer to \"Transfer Admission Screening Policy\" below. Additional preparatory coursework listed in the “Recommended Preparation” section are not required for admission, but are strongly recommended. Completion of these courses will help ensure timely progress toward degree completion. More information and a list of screening majors and non-screening majors may be found on the Admissions website.",
    "The UC Santa Cruz Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate (IB), and A-Level examination credit policies may be found in the UC Santa Cruz General Catalog . AP, IBH, and A-level exams may or may not satisfy course requirements, depending on the specific exam."
